---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Positronikal - Digital Forensics & Cybersecurity Research">
  <div class="cli-window animate-terminal-startup">
    <!-- Terminal Header -->
    <div class="cli-header">
      <div class="cli-traffic-lights">
        <div class="cli-traffic-light bg-red-500"></div>
        <div class="cli-traffic-light bg-yellow-500"></div>
        <div class="cli-traffic-light bg-green-500"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-terminal-green text-xs font-mono">Positronikal Terminal v1.0.0</div>
      <div class="w-16"></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Terminal Body -->
    <div class="cli-body">
      <!-- Welcome Message -->
      <div class="terminal-welcome animate-fade-in">
        <div class="ascii-art text-terminal-matrix-green mb-6">
██████╗  ██████╗ ███████╗██╗████████╗██████╗  ██████╗ ███╗   ██╗██╗██╗  ██╗ █████╗ ██╗     
██╔══██╗██╔═══██╗██╔════╝██║╚══██╔══╝██╔══██╗██╔═══██╗████╗  ██║██║██║ ██╔╝██╔══██╗██║     
██████╔╝██║   ██║███████╗██║   ██║   ██████╔╝██║   ██║██╔██╗ ██║██║█████╔╝ ███████║██║     
██╔═══╝ ██║   ██║╚════██║██║   ██║   ██╔══██╗██║   ██║██║╚██╗██║██║██╔═██╗ ██╔══██║██║     
██║     ╚██████╔╝███████║██║   ██║   ██║  ██║╚██████╔╝██║ ╚████║██║██║  ██╗██║  ██║███████╗
╚═╝      ╚═════╝ ╚══════╝╚═╝   ╚═╝   ╚═╝  ╚═╝ ╚═════╝ ╚═╝  ╚═══╝╚═╝╚═╝  ╚═╝╚═╝  ╚═╝╚══════╝
        </div>

        <h1 class="text-terminal-yellow text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-6 glitch" data-text="Welcome to Positronikal">
          Welcome to Positronikal
        </h1>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Introduction -->
          <div class="cyber-card">
            <p class="text-terminal-white text-lg leading-relaxed">
              Welcome to <span class="text-terminal-yellow font-bold">Positronikal</span> on GitHub! 
              My real name is <span class="text-terminal-cyan">Hoyt Harness</span>, but Positronikal 
              is the moniker I've used for several years for my digital projects.
            </p>
            
            <p class="text-terminal-gray mt-4">
              The majority of projects I host here pertain to <span class="text-terminal-matrix-green">digital forensics</span> 
              and <span class="text-terminal-matrix-green">cyber investigation</span>. That said, there will likely 
              also be projects that don't directly pertain to these subject matter areas.
            </p>

            <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-terminal-info-cyan bg-opacity-20 border border-terminal-info-cyan border-opacity-30 rounded">
              <p class="text-terminal-info-cyan text-sm">
                <strong>Note:</strong> I continue to host public forks of other projects from my personal account at 
                <a href="https://github.com/hoyt-harness" class="text-terminal-yellow hover:text-terminal-white">
                  github.com/hoyt-harness
                </a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Featured Projects Section -->
          <div class="cyber-card">
            <h2 class="text-terminal-yellow text-2xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-terminal-matrix-green mr-2">🔍</span>
              Featured Projects
            </h2>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <!-- EWF Tools -->
              <div class="project-card">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-white font-bold">libewf-legacy-win</h3>
                  <span class="project-status status-active">Active</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-terminal-gray text-sm mb-3">
                  Expert Witness Format tools for Windows AMD64. Complete build environment 
                  with Visual Studio 2022 support and pre-built binaries.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                  <a href="https://github.com/Positronikal/libewf-legacy-win" 
                     class="project-link block">
                    → View Repository
                  </a>
                  <p class="text-xs text-terminal-cyan">
                    Forked from libyal/libewf-legacy with Windows-specific enhancements
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Simple Backup -->
              <div class="project-card">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-white font-bold">simpleBackup</h3>
                  <span class="project-status status-active">Active</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-terminal-gray text-sm mb-3">
                  Simple backup utility for Debian-based distros using rsync and dialog. 
                  Clean, efficient, and easily extensible.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                  <a href="https://github.com/Positronikal/simpleBackup" 
                     class="project-link block">
                    → View Repository
                  </a>
                  <p class="text-xs text-terminal-cyan">
                    Bash-based with room for community expansion
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- MacPorts Assistant -->
              <div class="project-card">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-white font-bold">macportsAssistant</h3>
                  <span class="project-status status-maintenance">Maintenance</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-terminal-gray text-sm mb-3">
                  macOS version-agnostic MacPorts installation and upgrade automation. 
                  Evolved from montereyMacports.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                  <a href="https://github.com/Positronikal/macportsAssistant" 
                     class="project-link block">
                    → View Repository
                  </a>
                  <p class="text-xs text-terminal-cyan">
                    Tested on macOS Ventura, backward compatible
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- CarnivoreLE -->
              <div class="project-card opacity-60">
                <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-white font-bold">CarnivoreLE</h3>
                  <span class="project-status status-deprecated">Deprecated</span>
                </div>
                <p class="text-terminal-gray text-sm mb-3">
                  Historical network packet capture tool. Deprecated as of December 31, 2020. 
                  Maintained for reference only.
                </p>
                <div class="space-y-2">
                  <a href="https://github.com/Positronikal/CarnivoreLE" 
                     class="project-link block">
                    → View Archive
                  </a>
                  <p class="text-xs text-terminal-error-red">
                    No new changes or pull requests accepted
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-terminal-forensics-blue bg-opacity-20 border border-terminal-forensics-blue border-opacity-30 rounded">
              <p class="text-terminal-cyan text-sm">
                💡 <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Type <code class="text-terminal-yellow">projects</code> in the terminal above 
                for detailed project information, or use commands like <code class="text-terminal-yellow">ewftools</code>, 
                <code class="text-terminal-yellow">backup</code>, etc.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Contributing Section -->
          <div class="cyber-card">
            <h2 class="text-terminal-yellow text-2xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-terminal-matrix-green mr-2">🤝</span>
              Contributing
            </h2>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="security-alert">
                <h3 class="text-terminal-error-red font-bold mb-2">🔐 Security Requirements</h3>
                <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-terminal-white text-sm">
                  <li><strong>GPG signatures required:</strong> All commits in pull requests must be GPG signed</li>
                  <li><strong>DCO compliance:</strong> Developer Certificate of Origin must be on file</li>
                  <li><strong>Key verification:</strong> Use of a keyserver is highly recommended</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-matrix-green font-bold mb-2">Getting Started:</h3>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-terminal-gray text-sm">
                    <li><a href="https://help.github.com/" class="text-terminal-yellow">GitHub Help</a> pages</li>
                    <li><a href="https://help.github.com/categories/bootcamp/" class="text-terminal-yellow">Bootcamp</a> quick start</li>
                    <li><a href="https://help.github.com/categories/setup" class="text-terminal-yellow">Setup</a> information</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-terminal-matrix-green font-bold mb-2">Standards:</h3>
                  <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-terminal-gray text-sm">
                    <li><a href="https://www.gnu.org/prep/standards/" class="text-terminal-yellow">GNU Coding Standards</a></li>
                    <li><a href="http://catb.org/esr/writings/taoup/html/" class="text-terminal-yellow">UNIX Philosophy</a></li>
                    <li>Clean, documented code</li>
                    <li>Security-first approach</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="dco-requirement">
                <h3 class="text-terminal-warning-amber font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="mr-2">📋</span>
                  Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO)
                </h3>
                <p class="text-terminal-white text-sm mb-3">
                  All contributors must sign and submit the Developer Certificate of Origin (DCO) before 
                  their contributions can be accepted. The DCO is a legally binding statement that you 
                  have the right to submit your contribution and agree to the project's licensing terms.
                </p>
                <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:space-x-4 space-y-2 sm:space-y-0">
                  <a href="/Posi_DCO.md" 
                     class="inline-flex items-center text-terminal-yellow hover:text-terminal-white font-bold transition-colors duration-200"
                     target="_blank"
                     rel="noopener noreferrer">
                    <span class="mr-2">📄</span>
                    Download DCO Template
                  </a>
                  <span class="text-terminal-gray text-xs">
                    (Fill out and include with your first contribution)
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="gpg-signature">
                <h3 class="text-terminal-forensics-blue font-bold mb-2">🔑 GPG Public Key</h3>
                <p class="text-terminal-gray text-sm">
                  My public key (Hoyt Harness) can be retrieved from MIT's keyserver at 
                  <a href="https://pgp.mit.edu/" class="text-terminal-yellow">pgp.mit.edu</a>. 
                  Use <code class="text-terminal-cyan">gpg</code> command in the terminal for detailed information.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Terminal Usage Tips -->
          <div class="cyber-card">
            <h2 class="text-terminal-yellow text-2xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-terminal-matrix-green mr-2">💻</span>
              Terminal Commands
            </h2>

            <p class="text-terminal-white mb-4">
              This site features a fully interactive terminal interface. Try these commands:
            </p>

            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 font-mono text-sm">
              <div>
                <h4 class="text-terminal-cyan font-bold mb-2">Information:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-terminal-gray">
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">help</code> - All commands</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">about</code> - About me</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">whoami</code> - User info</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">neofetch</code> - System info</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="text-terminal-cyan font-bold mb-2">Projects:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-terminal-gray">
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">projects</code> - List all</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">ewftools</code> - EWF details</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">backup</code> - Backup tool</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">macports</code> - MacPorts</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div>
                <h4 class="text-terminal-cyan font-bold mb-2">Security:</h4>
                <ul class="space-y-1 text-terminal-gray">
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">gpg</code> - GPG info</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">dco</code> - DCO requirements</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">security</code> - Policies</li>
                  <li><code class="text-terminal-yellow">contact</code> - Contact info</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-terminal-matrix-green bg-opacity-10 border border-terminal-matrix-green border-opacity-30 rounded">
              <p class="text-terminal-matrix-green text-sm">
                🎯 <strong>Keyboard shortcuts:</strong> Tab for completion, ↑/↓ for history, Ctrl+L to clear, Ctrl+` to focus terminal
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- License -->
          <div class="mt-8 text-center">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 mb-4">
              <a rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">
                <img alt="Creative Commons License" 
                     class="border-0" 
                     src="https://i.creativecommons.org/l/by/4.0/88x31.png" />
              </a>
              <span class="text-terminal-gray text-sm">
                This work is licensed under a 
                <a rel="license" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/" class="text-terminal-yellow">
                  Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
                </a>
              </span>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Attribution Credit -->
            <div class="text-terminal-gray text-xs opacity-75">
              <p class="mb-1">
                Terminal interface concept inspired by the excellent work of 
                <a href="https://github.com/m-mdy-m" class="text-terminal-cyan hover:text-terminal-white transition-colors duration-200">0x (m-mdy-m)</a>
              </p>
              <p>
                Original portfolio: <a href="https://m-mdy-m.github.io/" class="text-terminal-cyan hover:text-terminal-white transition-colors duration-200">m-mdy-m.github.io</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>